# Cursor rules — TRELYAN verify-pqc SDK

FOLLOW `AGENTS.md` in this repo root. It is the source of truth; these are the highlights Cursor must obey.

HARD rules (do not violate):
- Crypto ONLY via @noble/post-quantum + @noble/curves + @noble/hashes. No new runtime deps.
- 0-downgrade / only-upgrade: additive changes only. `PQC_SKIP_LIVE=1 node test-all.mjs` must print "ALL MODULES PASS" before any commit; modules may be added, never silently removed (MIN_MODULES ratchet).
- Every module's `canon()` is byte-identical to the reference (sorted-key, type-distinct) — see AGENTS.md.
- Verifiers are TOTAL/fail-closed: wrap in try/catch, return {verified:false} on bad input, never throw.
- Hybrid signing is AND-composition: all legs (Ed25519 ∧ ML-DSA-87 ∧ SLH-DSA) must verify; stripping any leg fails.
- Unique domain-separation context string per module (`trelyan-<module>-v1`).
- Each module ships a self-test and is wired into test-all.mjs.

Honesty (claims must be falsifiable): NEVER "military-grade"/"unbreakable"/"FIPS-validated"/"quantum-proof". Say "downgrade-detecting under the declared trust model" / "tamper-evident" / "unaudited reference implementation". Canonical QLR ledger = Algorand; liboqs is NOT NIST-certified; NERION is software+cloud-KMS not HSM-backed.

Secrets: never put secrets in code/logs; .env stays out of git; never stage .env/_scratch*.

Code-gen helper: StarCoder2 via `python -m apex_jarvis.tools.starcoder2` (completion / --infill). Code model only — not for architecture/security reasoning.
